node.text: Topped with a colorful mix of tropical fruit, toasted nuts, and seeds, these open-faced chocolate disks from chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) can be made ahead and served right from the fridge. Plus, they come together with the help of none other than your microwave! Find out how to make Tropical Mendiants by visiting this link https://bit.ly/2VLcZMq or tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.text: The secret to these flavor-packed, plant-based nachos from @chefmamacass2 are two different kinds of lentils: black and red. Crispy pita chips are smothered with an the irresistable feta queso, layers of pepper-tinged lentil chili, rose harissa-spiked pickled cabbage, and dollops of yogurt. It's definitely a dish worth sharing. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.title: FWCooks | Loaded Pita Nachos with Lentil Chili and Feta Queso

Find out how to add some 'cue to your greens through the link in bio.

🍽️: @paigegrandjean 📸: @jencausey

node.text: Need a dessert that’s easy to make and pleases a crowd? Chef Paola Velez’ (@smallorchids) Tropical Mendiants will definitely do the trick. The colorful and delicious chocolate disks can be made ahead, be served right from the fridge, and call for just a microwave instead of a stovetop. Try the latest #PastriesWithPaola creation through the link in bio! 📸: @reallyfarrah

node.text: On this episode of Chefs At Home, @dan_churchill of @charleyst combines a melange of mushrooms, broccoli, tofu, and wine to create a hearty filling for his Aussie Meat(less) Pie in an ode to his home country, @australia. The buttery and tender handrolled crust is the golden crown on this plant-powered gem. Tap the link in bio to watch the full episode on YouTube! #Sponsored

Both beautiful and economical, this Tomatoes with Herbs and Almond Vinaigrette recipe is a keeper. Onion and jalapeno join toasted almonds for a bit of crunch while richly flavored oil makes a nice, tangy dressing for this total summer showstopper. 
🍽️: @dan_kluger 📸: @johnkernick

Seared Salmon with Summer Vegetables was one of the most popular items on the menu at @unionsquarecafe and one of the best recipes we ever published. The myriad vegetables in this recipe—corn, spinach, shiitakes, and tomato—sing of warm sunny days. Tap the link in bio to taste summer one more time! 
🍽️: Michael Romano 📸: @gregdupree

node.text: Topped with a colorful mix of tropical fruit, toasted nuts, and seeds, these open-faced chocolate disks from chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) can be made ahead and served right from the fridge. Plus, they come together with the help of none other than your microwave! Find out how to make Tropical Mendiants by visiting this link https://bit.ly/2VLcZMq or tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.text: Have some leftover tomato paste lying around? Well, we have some ideas on how to put the classic pantry staple to use. From customized Bloody Mary mix to vinaigrettes and marinades, tap the link in bio for helpful suggestions to get the most out of that little can (or tube). 📸: @gettyimages

node.text:
Give a round of applause to these super-simple, indulgent Gooey Chocolate-Chip Sandwich Bars. Two layers of chocolate chip cookie dough are sandwiched with a decadent fudgy filling and baked until browned. Tap the link in bio for your next baking project! 
🍽️: Sally Sampson 📸: @alphamay

node.text: This Pasta with Roasted Sun Gold Tomato Sauce from F&W Associate Features Editor @ninafriend is a smart and delicious way to put those summer tomatoes to use. Get the recipe for this stunning orange-hued sauce through the link in bio! 📸: @linda.xiao
